4:
Does anyone else hear that? Could
someone be fighting nearby?
14:
Oh! Hey there, didn't expect to run
into you guys so soon! Talk about
great timing!
30:
I'd love to give you an explanation,
but...
36:
Sorry, could you help me clean this
up first?
41:
Doesn't seem like we can say no
anyway!
47:
Guess I can be frank since you're
already in the know: I'm here on
Society business.
50:
That is the organization you're a part
of, yes? The one that hunts primal
beasts?
56:
Exactly. You remember the trouble
we had when those primal beasts
from our world got sucked into yours?
58:
That hole they came through is still
open. That's how I got here.
61:
If that's the case... Are you implying
that more primal beasts might
appear in our world?
67:
Possibly, but even if they do, I bet it
won't be that often. Still, the
higher-ups are kinda worried about
any further incidents.
70:
This world's not properly equipped
to handle primal beasts, so
contractors like me will be checking
in on things occasionally.
75:
Then you're here just on lookout
duty? No other jobs or anything?
79:
Yeah. Honestly, I see this as mostly a
vacation, all things considered.
84: Time to kick back and relax?
88:
You betcha. I'm gonna squeeze out
as much fun as I can out of this!
91:
Speaking of which, mind letting me
crash in Starview while I'm here?
105:
Thanks a bunch! I really lucked out
running into you guys so quickly.
108:
By the way, if you ever need any
help with anything, don't be a
stranger. You scratch my back, 
I scratch yours!
113:
That reminds me. You guys were
gathering these, right?
117:
Take it. Hopefully it covers at least
some of my living expenses.
122:
SOME? You could probably afford a
fancy hotel for weeks with this much!
127:
Haha, you're really something else,
huh?
130:
Excuse me, we couldn't help but
overhear... Did you say YOU
gathered all those elemental gems?
132:
That's amazing! You know, someone
skilled like you should join us!
135:
Eh, sorry, I'll pass. I'm already spoken
for.
138:
You sure? We're actually pretty
famous around these parts. Got
connections and stuff you could use.
141:
I don't care what's on the tableI'm
with this crew.
144:
I won't ditch them for any amount of
money or info you've got on offer.
147: So take good care of me, guys!
156:
How's a welcoming party sound? Is
there anything in particular you'd
like to eat?
160:
Talk about a harsh rejection. You
sure you're fine sticking with us?
164:
Of course I am. There's no replacing
someone you can count on to cover
your back, you know?
166:
Trust isn't something money can
buy. Besides, I know you're reliable
on the battlefield, AND you seem like
you can handle Bea when she's
being stupid.
169: That's the part that matters to you?
173:
Not just that. Seriously, the Society
could use people like you.
177:
How about it, Alk? If you join us, you'll
have access to cool weapons like
mine and awesome coworkers to
show you the ropes.
182:
U-uh, I'm not sure I'd be the best
candidate...
186:
Hey now, none of that. Or are you
saying I've got faulty judgment?
190:
...Sorry, you're right. I shouldn't put
myself down like that. The offer's
appreciated, but...
194: I've still got things I need to do here.
198:
Yeah, I figured as much. It was worth
a shot, though.
202:
At the very least, I'll help out
whenever you need a hand in our
world. Promise.
206:
Yeah? I'll definitely be taking you up
on that offer...
209:
Starting with finding us something
nice to eat. Then you can introduce
me to all the best shopping areas
around, and... What else...
214:
Your immediate request is for a
tour?!
217:
And one that's going to be long, by
the sound of it...
222: Good luck, pal. You're gonna need it.
227:
Come on, you can't expect me to
work hard without playing hard too.
232: This sounds like it will be a lot of fun.
240:
Now come on! Let's get this vacation
started!
